{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-changelog-js","path":"/changelog/2019/may","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h3 id=\"program-dashboard\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#program-dashboard\" aria-label=\"program dashboard permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Program Dashboard</h3>\n<p>Weâ€™ve revamped the Program Dashboard with new metric tables and charts that give better insight into reporting and analytics for programs.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 500px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 52%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"program dashboard\"\n        title=\"program dashboard\"\n        src=\"/static/f73245ede20e6c45b15846f4f8c9234c/0b533/may_2019_program_dashboard.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f73245ede20e6c45b15846f4f8c9234c/fac75/may_2019_program_dashboard.png 125w,\n/static/f73245ede20e6c45b15846f4f8c9234c/63868/may_2019_program_dashboard.png 250w,\n/static/f73245ede20e6c45b15846f4f8c9234c/0b533/may_2019_program_dashboard.png 500w,\n/static/f73245ede20e6c45b15846f4f8c9234c/1d69c/may_2019_program_dashboard.png 750w,\n/static/f73245ede20e6c45b15846f4f8c9234c/00d43/may_2019_program_dashboard.png 1000w,\n/static/f73245ede20e6c45b15846f4f8c9234c/bc81a/may_2019_program_dashboard.png 2862w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"enhancements-to-the-jira-integration\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#enhancements-to-the-jira-integration\" aria-label=\"enhancements to the jira integration permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Enhancements to the Jira Integration</h3>\n<p>We've added these improvements to the bi-directional Jira integration:</p>\n<h4 id=\"additional-fields\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#additional-fields\" aria-label=\"additional fields permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Additional Fields</h4>\n<p>The HackerOne to Jira escalation template now includes all additional fields that are either a type of <code>string</code>, <code>number</code>, or <code>date</code>. This enables Jira users to have all fields in Jira be mapped to a value from the HackerOne report. All available Jira fields will automatically be pulled from the selected issue type.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 500px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 104.80000000000001%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"additional fields wen escalating HackerOne to Jira\"\n        title=\"additional fields wen escalating HackerOne to Jira\"\n        src=\"/static/85a818a8d7f6161366b11c60964a4425/0b533/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_additional-fields.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/85a818a8d7f6161366b11c60964a4425/fac75/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_additional-fields.png 125w,\n/static/85a818a8d7f6161366b11c60964a4425/63868/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_additional-fields.png 250w,\n/static/85a818a8d7f6161366b11c60964a4425/0b533/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_additional-fields.png 500w,\n/static/85a818a8d7f6161366b11c60964a4425/1d69c/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_additional-fields.png 750w,\n/static/85a818a8d7f6161366b11c60964a4425/00d43/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_additional-fields.png 1000w,\n/static/85a818a8d7f6161366b11c60964a4425/3f8cf/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_additional-fields.png 1293w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h4 id=\"sync-attachments\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#sync-attachments\" aria-label=\"sync attachments permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Sync Attachments</h4>\n<p>Jira users can now sync attachments from their HackerOne report to Jira by selecting <strong>Synchronize attachments</strong> in the <strong>Select HackerOne to Jira events</strong> section when configuring their Jira integration.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 500px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 69.60000000000001%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"synchronize attachments option in the jira integration\"\n        title=\"synchronize attachments option in the jira integration\"\n        src=\"/static/55c02cfc807929a4039cf785522b56ac/0b533/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_sync-attachments.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/55c02cfc807929a4039cf785522b56ac/fac75/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_sync-attachments.png 125w,\n/static/55c02cfc807929a4039cf785522b56ac/63868/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_sync-attachments.png 250w,\n/static/55c02cfc807929a4039cf785522b56ac/0b533/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_sync-attachments.png 500w,\n/static/55c02cfc807929a4039cf785522b56ac/1d69c/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_sync-attachments.png 750w,\n/static/55c02cfc807929a4039cf785522b56ac/00d43/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_sync-attachments.png 1000w,\n/static/55c02cfc807929a4039cf785522b56ac/c45c7/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_sync-attachments.png 1346w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h4 id=\"automated-report-closure\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#automated-report-closure\" aria-label=\"automated report closure permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Automated Report Closure</h4>\n<p>Jira users can now select which Jira closed issue status should result in the closure of the HackerOne report.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 500px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 71.2%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"automating report closure with Jira\"\n        title=\"automating report closure with Jira\"\n        src=\"/static/7f39ab3e6273436dee6c1820f13f80de/0b533/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_report-closure.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7f39ab3e6273436dee6c1820f13f80de/fac75/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_report-closure.png 125w,\n/static/7f39ab3e6273436dee6c1820f13f80de/63868/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_report-closure.png 250w,\n/static/7f39ab3e6273436dee6c1820f13f80de/0b533/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_report-closure.png 500w,\n/static/7f39ab3e6273436dee6c1820f13f80de/1d69c/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_report-closure.png 750w,\n/static/7f39ab3e6273436dee6c1820f13f80de/00d43/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_report-closure.png 1000w,\n/static/7f39ab3e6273436dee6c1820f13f80de/c45c7/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_report-closure.png 1346w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h4 id=\"severity-to-priority-mapping\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#severity-to-priority-mapping\" aria-label=\"severity to priority mapping permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Severity to Priority Mapping</h4>\n<p>With severity to priority mapping, Jira users can map HackerOne severity ratings to the priority fields they have in Jira. This enables the right priority to be set when escalating a report to Jira.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 500px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 47.199999999999996%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"severity to priority mapping\"\n        title=\"severity to priority mapping\"\n        src=\"/static/e4107103316c781c7c218ca2a0745884/0b533/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_severity-priority-mapping.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e4107103316c781c7c218ca2a0745884/fac75/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_severity-priority-mapping.png 125w,\n/static/e4107103316c781c7c218ca2a0745884/63868/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_severity-priority-mapping.png 250w,\n/static/e4107103316c781c7c218ca2a0745884/0b533/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_severity-priority-mapping.png 500w,\n/static/e4107103316c781c7c218ca2a0745884/1d69c/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_severity-priority-mapping.png 750w,\n/static/e4107103316c781c7c218ca2a0745884/00d43/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_severity-priority-mapping.png 1000w,\n/static/e4107103316c781c7c218ca2a0745884/78612/may_2019_jira%2B%2B_severity-priority-mapping.png 1260w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>","frontmatter":{"path":"/changelog/2019/may","title":"May 2019"}}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}